{"/service/ndnp/ncu/batch_ncu_lagarde_ver02/data/sn99061530/00332892605/1958051601/1133.xml":{"full_text":"FRIDAY, MAY 16, 1958\nCLASSIFIED\n\u2022ADVERTISING.\nADVERTISING IN THESE COLUMNS COSTS THREE CENTS PER\nWORD, FIRST INSERTION; ALL INSERTIONS AFTER FIRST, TWO\nCENTS PER WORD. MINIMUM CHARGE IS 50 CENTS. IF YOU\nWANT TO BUY, RENT, SELL, SWAP, GET A JOB, HIRE HELP,\nFIND SOMETHING LOST, THE CLASSIFIEDS OFFER AN EFFEC\nTIVE AND ECONOMICAL MEDIUM.\nVisit ANDERSON\u2019S SUPER\nMARKET-BEACH STORE at\ntwo mile post. Vacation headquar\nters. Open year \u2019round. Write\nBILL ANDERSON\u2019S RENTAL\nAGENCY, KITTY HAWK, reser\nvations, oceanfront housekeeping\ncottages* T-4-8-tfc\nHOME IMPROVEMENTS\u2014Roof\ning, siding, garages built, rooms\nadded, baths installed complete,\nbrick and cement work, painting\nor anything else you want to im\nprove your home. Pay nothing\ndown, 36 months to pay. See\nCharles Haskett or phone 5704\nElizabeth City. T-8-9-tfc\nOFFICE SUPPLIES, PRINTING\norders for printing of all kinds\nfilled .promptly. We print forms,\nblanks, letterheads, statements, en\nvelopes. Order from your Pilot and\nHerald Agent, or Times Printing\nCo., Manteo, N. C. We carry book\nkeeping supplies, and some office\nfurniture.\nte-.\nINDEPENDENT insurance agen\ncies can and will \u201cserve you\nfirst\u201d Contact us for yours now.\nHugh Fortescue, Washington.\nTPH-8-29-tfc\nCAMELLIAS, azaleas, hollies, va\nriety of evergreen plants 1.00\nup; Pyracantha (red berried) 1.00;\nnice flowering trees and shrubs;\nJuniper, Cypress, Arborvitae; Let\nus help you to make your home\nmore beautiful. Roanoke Island\nGardens, Manteo, N. C. Corner\nMother Vineyard Rd. T-l-24-tfc\nPICK-UP TRUCK, late model half\nton Chevrolet, 30,000 miles, new\nrubber all around, radio and heat\ner. Times Printing Co., Manteo, N.\nC. T-5-23t\nHELP WANTED\u2014Do you want a\ngood, profitable and permanent\nbusiness of your own in Hyde and\nTyrrell Counties? Write Raw\nleigh's, Dept. NCE-480-565-A,\nRichmond, Va. PH-5-l-stp\nFOR SALE: Hatteras Village. 11,2I 1 ,2\nacres, 3 houses (two 1-bedroom;\none 4-bedroom) frame construc\ntion, waterfront. E. E. Meekins,\nrealtor, phone Manteo 101.\nT-5-2-3tc\nSEASHORE VACATIONS on Hat\nteras Island near Oregon Inlet,\nat low cost family-style boarding.\nPhone 130, Mirlo Beach Lodge, Ro\ndanthe. Write for information.\nARTIFICIAL BREEDING of your\ncows to purebred, proven stocks\nis both profitable and economical.\nThis service available to family\ncow owners, beef producers, dairy\nherds. All dairy and beef breeds\navailable. Call H. E. Clayton, Bel\nhaven WH 3-3206. P-10-4-tfc\nSAVE YOUR FLOORS and nice\ntile; use plastic and rubber cups\ncinder your desk and furniture legs.\nAll sizes in stock. Times Printing\nCo., Manteo, N. C.\nFor your insurance needs see\nW. R. PEARCE, Manteo, N. C.\nAll kinds of insurance\nOCRACOKE, N. C. FOR RENT:\nJune and August, furnished,\nWahab-Williams homestead, seven\nbedrooms; by week, week end or\nmonth. Houseparties. Rates rea\nsonable. Contract Mrs. Nina W.\nWarren, 636 Massachusetts Ave.,\nTel. Madison 7-2792, Norfolk, Va.\nT-5-9-2tc\nFOR SALE: 260\u2019 frontage north\nof Salvo, highway to Park Sei-v\n--ice line. E. E. Meekins, realtor,\nphone Manteo 101. T-5-2-3tc\nWURLITZER SPINET Piano at\nNags Head real bargain. Custo\nmer. giving up on account health.\nTake up payments on balance due\nsave us picking it up. E. R.\nPOOLE MUSIC COMPANY, RA\nLEIGH, N. C. T-4-25-7tc\nPETUNIAS, Salvia, 1.50 doz;\nSweet William SI.OO Doz.;\nDouble Petunias, Ageratums, Bro\nwallias, $2.00 Doz. Verbena.\nColeus, Lantana, Saltana, 25<\u2018 each;\nalso, geraniums, begonias, fuchias,\ni 1 achyranthus, ivies, foliage plants,\netc. Roanoke Island Gardens,\nPhone 210-J, Manteo, N. C.\nT-5-9-6tc\nPHONE Manteo 366-J2 for refrig\neration, air-conditioning, motor re\npairs, day or night. Jimmie\u2019s Re\nfrigeration, W. M. \u201cJimmie\u201d\nUmphlett. T-5-9-4tp\nHOUSE AND TRACT of land for\nsale, Stumpy Point, N. 'C. Apply\nto Edna Nixon Bernick, 346 Fair\nfax Ave., Norfolk, Va., Phone\nMA-75038 after 6 p'.fn. for infor\nmation. 5-15-3tc\nTO'HAVE YOUR lawn mowed, call\nPaul Mayo, Manteo 73-J.\nT-4-25-4tc\nWOMAN WANTED itflr waitress\nwork. Owen\u2019s Restaurant, Nags\nHead, N. C. Phone 8651.\nY-4-25-Btc\nCO2 fire extinguishers, S2O each\nor two for $35. USCG approved.\nG. G. Bonner, General'Supply Co.,\nManteo. Tel. 4-W. T-11-8-tfc\nFOR SALE: Mashoes\u20142 bedroom\nfurnished house, frame construc\ntion, ideal for fishing and hunting.\nSound frontage. E. E. Meekins,\nrealtor, phone Manteo 101.\nT-5-2-3tc\nTHE OLD SEA CAPTAIN AND\nDRUMMER Book sl, postpaid.\nGet this racy book of dialogue\nfrom Cape Hatteras and the N. C.\nCoastland. Send it to your friends,\n6 copies $5 postpaid. Times Print\ning Co.. Inc., Manteo, N. C.\nGET-WELL CARDS See our\nnew assortments, just arrived, both\nserious and humorous. TIMES\nPRINTING COMPANY, Manteo.\nREAL ESTATE on Coast. If in\nterested in buying or selling\nCoastal property of any kind, try\nthe MIRLO CO., Phone 244, Man\nteo, N. C.\nRUBBER STAMPS made to order,\nstamp pads, etc. Leave orders at\nPilot and Herald Office, in Bel\nhaven or Swan Quarter.\nLAWN MOWER REPAIRING. We\nrepair all makes of lawnmowers\nand small gasoline engines. Parts\navailable for all makes and models.\nSatisfaction guaranteed. ALEX\u2019S\nREPAIR SHOP, Wanchese, N. C.\nPhone 248-J2. T-5-2-tfc\nFOR SALE: Building site in Town\nof Manteo 71\u2019 x 159\u2019. E. E.\nMeekins, realtor ,phone Manteo\n101. T-5-2-3tc\nBE A SUCCESS, Earn a weekly\nincome taking care of Avon cus\ntomers in Avon, Waves, Salvo, Ro\ndanthe. Write Mrs. Latham, Box\n681, Greenville, N. C. T-5-9-3tc\nTYPEWRITERS, rebuilt and re\nconditioned, sold at less than\nmail order prices. All makes in\nstock. The Pilot and Herald, Bel\nhaven, N. C. or Times Printing Co.,\nManteo.\nFOR RENT\u2014Three bedroom house\nunfurnished, on hard-surfaced\nroad near Manteo. E. E. Meekins,\nPhone 101, Manteo. N. C.\nT-5-9-3tc\nWANTED\u2014Man with car between\nthe ages of 25 to 55 to handle\na Watkins Business Business in\nHyde County. Dealer willing to\ninvest 5 days a week in handling\nhis own business can make above\naverage earnings. Products Na\ntionally Advertised. Field help\nprovided. Free Insurance. Com\npany now celebrating 90th year\nin business with great dividend\ndeals. Business is permanent and\nprofitable with no layoffs for the\nman who wants to operate his\nown business with Company capi\ntal. For full narticulars write to\nday to The J. R. Watkins Com\noany, P. O. Box 5071, Richmond,\nVirginia. PH-5-15-stc\nMAN OR WOMAN\u2014Established\nWatkins Route Available in Bel\nhaven\u2014no experience necessary in\nthis area. Write P. O. Box 5071,\nDepartment 8-3, Richmond, Va.\nPH-5-15-3tp\nARTISTS SUPPLIES. Speed ball\nsets, India ink, black drawing\nink, silver ink. white ink. drawing\npaper. TIMES PRINTING CO.,\nInc.. Manteo. tc\nCANDIDATE FOR CORONER\nI hereby offer myself as a Can\ndidate for Coroner of Dare Coun\nty, subject to the Democratic Pri\nmary on May 31, 1958.\nYour support on that date will\nbe greatly appreciated.\nJAMES M. VANNOTE\nT-5-16-3tc\nNOTICE\nNORTH CAROLINA\nDARE COUNTY\nIN THE SUPERIOR COURT\nMELVIN L. BRAGG, Plaintiff\nvs.\nVIRGINIA D. BRAGG, Defendant\nThe above named defendant, Vir\nginia D. Bregg, will take notice\nthat an action entitled as above\nhas been commenced in the Super\nior Court of Dare County, North\nCarolina, by the plaintiff to secure\nan absolute divorce from the de\nfendant upon the ground that\nplaintiff and defendant have lived\nseparate and apart for more than\ntwo years next preceding the\nbringing of this action; and the\ndefendant will further take notice\nthat she is required to ap\nf>ear at the office of the\nClerk of the Superior Court\nof Dare County, in the court\nhouse in Manteo, North Carolina,\nwithin twenty days after the 23rd\nday of May. 1958, and answer or\ndemur to the complaint in said\naction, or the plaintiff will app\u2019y\nto the Court for the relief de\nmanded in said conjplairit\nT ,ia6 h c d *v\u00bbr\nClerk Superior Court\nT-4-25-4W\nSTATEMENT BY\nDAVID STICK\nFOR COUNTY COMMISSIONER\nATLANTIC TOWNSHIP 1\nI have filed as a candidate\nfor Commissioner from Atlantic\nTownship subject to the Demo\ncratic primary.\nI am associated with no political\nclique, nor am I bound by promises\nto any individual or special group,\nand except for my wife no one\nwas consulted concerning my de\ncision to run for this office.\nIn the event the voters of Dare\nCounty should elect me to this\nposition, I promise them simply\nthat I will not come under the\ndomination of any so-called politi\ncal leader; that I will do my best\nto approach each new problem\nwith an open mind; that I will\nmake my final decision in each\ninstance on the basis of what I\nfeel is best for the prosperity,\nprogress and well being of Dare\nCounty as a whole; that I will\nstate my position clearly on each\nissue as it arises; and that I will\nconduct my public business in pub\nlic and not behind closed doors.\nAs a resident of Dare County\nsince 1929 I have attempted to\nparticipate in civic activities when\never called on, to keep well inform\ned on county affairs, and to learn\nas much as I cohid about the pres\nent and future needs of the county.\nI feel that my past experience as\na reporter covering the county\ngovernment in Manteo, the State\nCapitol in Raleigh, and the Na\ntional Capitol in Washington, and\nas a writer concentrating on the\nhistory of Dare County, would be\nuseful to a member of the Board\nof County Commissioners.\nI do not solicit the vote of any\nindividual who would expect spe\ncial consideration from me in ex\nchange for such support.\nOn the basis of the above state\nment I submit my name to the\nvoters of Dare County.\nDAVID STICK\nColington\nT-5-2-stc\nROBERT O. BALLANCE SEEKS\nINTEREST OF THE VOTERS\nI wish to announce \u2019my candi\ndacy for the Board of Education,\nNags Head Township, Dare Coun\nty, subject to the Democratic Pri\nmary May 31, 1958.\nOur future depends upon our\nchildren; our children depend upon\nus, therefore they must be given\nevery opportunity available to ob\ntain a higher standard in educa\ntion. We hope by the first of Sep\ntember, 1958 the citizens of Dare\nCounty can realize three new\nschools in the last four years. A\nnew elementary school at Kitty\nHawk, a new Cape Hatteras\nSchool at Buxton, a new high\nschool at Manteo and improve\nments on the Roanoke School. For\nseveral years prior to this, chil\ndren were attending schools con\ndemned by the State Department.\nWe have made great progress, but\nmuch more work and study is to\nbe done to bring us up on a higher\neducational level.\nFriends, attend your PTA meet\nings and all your school functions.\nSupport you J\u2019 teachers; they have\na tremendous job to do, and see\nthat your children attend school\nregularly.\nYour vote and support will be\nappreciated.\nROBERT O. BALLANCE\nBUS SCHEDULE\nBETWEEN MANTEO\nAND HATTERAS\nEffective April 1, 1958\nNORTHBOUND\nLv. Hatteras 9:00 A.M.\nAr. Manteo 11:45 A.M.\nSOUTHBOUND\nLv. Manteo 2:45 P.M.\nAr. Hatteras 5:45 P.M.\nCHARTERED TRIPS\nHATTERAS-MANTEO\nBUS LINE\nPhone 104 Hatteras, N. C.\nRAYMOND WHITE,\nCANDIDATE FOR\nCORONER IN DARE\nIn announcing my candidacy for the office of\nCoroner of Dare County subject to the action of\nthe Democratic primary, I wish to express my\nappreciation to the many people who have en\ncouraged me to run, who think I should win, and\nwho have pledged their support.\nI would enjoy, if it were possible for me to do\nso, to visit every person in the county. In many\n.years here with the people of the county, I have\nmade many associations, and I feel that they un\nderstand the situation, that I need no introduction.\nIf elected, I will faithfully perform such duties as\narise.\nSincerely yours,\nRAYMOND E. WHITE\nManteo, N. C.\nTHE COASTLAND TIMES, MANTEO, N. C.\nCANDIDATE for RE-ELECTION\nDARE COMMISSIONER\nI hereby announce my candidacy\nfor the office of County Commis\nsioner from Kennekeet Township,\nsubject to the action of the Demo\ncratic Primary, May 31.\nI wish to thank all the people\nfor their favors in the past, and\nto assure them I will apreciate\ntheir vote and support for re\nelection another term. I will give\nthe people the full benefit of my\nknowledge and ability,and try in\nevery way to serve the whole peo\nple, and I will see that the people\nof the township I represent will\nget their just share of what is due\nthem, as I have done in the past.\nI will appreciate your giving me\nyour views on all matters of pub\nlic interest. Sincerely yours,\nNEWCOMB MIDGETT\nWaves, N.C. May 14 1958\nNORTH CAROLINA\nDARE COUNTY\nBEFORE THE BOARD OF\nCOMMISSIONERS.\nDARE COUNTY\nNOTICE OF HEARING\nON A PETITION\nFOR ABANDONMENT\nOF STREET OR WAY\nRoanoke Sound Shores, Inc,\nPetitioner\nto\nDare County, Thomas Gilliam, 111,\net als\nAll persons having or claiming\nto have any light, title or interest\nin or to lands located in Nags\nHead Township, Dare County,\nNorth Carolina, formerly known as\nNags Head Beach property of\nNags Head Development Corpora\ntion, as shown on Map or Plat, re\ncorded in Map Book 1. pages 192-\n189, Office of the Register of\nDeeds, Dare County. North Caro\nlina, and the Roanoke Sound\nShores Inc. property shown on\nmap or plat thereof, recorded in\nMap Book 2, Page 90, Public Reg\nistry of Dare County, North Caro\nlina, and the public will take no\ntice that a petition has been filed\nwith this Board, the purpose of\nwhich is to abandon a certain\nstreet, way or right of wav, dedi\ncated to the public by plat, but\nunopened, unpaved and unused,\nwhich said area is situated to the\nNorth of Block C and South of\nBlock D, and running in an East-\nWest direction, and designated on\nthe plat of Petitioner\u2019s property\nas a 10 foot Lane, a copy of said\npetition is on file with the Clerk\nto the Board of Commissioners.\nAnd all such persons will take\nnotice that a hearing upon the\nPetition will be had at the June\nMeeting of the Board of Commis\nsioners, in the Court House in\nManteo. N. C. at 10:00 A.M. on\nTuesday, June 3, 1958.\nAnd all interested parties will\nfurther take notice that the Board\nwill act on said Petition at its\nJune meeting; and that all inter\nseted parties shall attend and make\nprotest, if any they have to said\npetition, or they would be bound by\nthe action of the Board, as by law*\nprovided, unless appeal is duly\nfiled before the said Board.\nNotice is hereby issued by\nauthority and at the direction of\nthe Board at its May meeting.\nThis 6th day of May, 1958.\nDARE COUNTY\nBOARD OF COMMISSIONERS\nBv Melvin R. Daniels\nClerk to the Board\nT-5-9-4tc\nGRAVEYARD OF\nTHE ATLANTIC\nBy DAVID STICK\nFactual Accounts of Numerous\nShipwrecks Along the\nOuter Banks\n$5.00 at Your Bookseller or\nfrom the Dare Press,\nKitty Hawk, N. C.\nHALLETT F. PERRY\nSEEKS RENOMINATION\nFOR COMMISSIONER\nI hereby announce my candidacy\nfor County Commissioner from At\nlantic Township, Dare County,\nN. C., subject to the Democrat Pri\nmary, May 31, 1958. I solicit your\nvote and support in the forthcom\ning election and if elected, promise\nto do my very best for all the\npeople of the County in all matters\ncoming before the Board for its\nconsideration. I believe I am com\npetent and capable of serving on\nhe Board of County Commission\ners, having had experience as a\nmember for several years.\nMy sole interest is to serve all\nsections of the County to the best\nof my ability and to see that every\none gets a square deal.\nYour vote and support will be\nappreciated.\nHALLETT F. PERRY\nKitty Hawk, N. C.\nADMINISTRATOR\u2019S NOTICE\nHaving qualified as Administra\ntrix of the estate of John Alford\nFarrow of Manteo, Dare County,\nNorth Carolina, this is to notify\nall persons having claims against\nthe estate of said John Alford\nFarrow to present them to the\nundersigned within one year from\ndate of this notice or same will be\npleaded in bar of their recovery.\nAll persons indebted to said estate\nplease make immediate payment.\nThis the sth dav of May. 1958.\nALICE F. MEEKINS\nAvon, N. C.\nT-5-9-6tc\nC.~C. DUVALL\nSEEKS RE-NOMINATION FOR\nCOUNTY COMMISSIONER\nI hereby announce my candidacy\nfor County Commissioner repre\nsenting Croatan Township, the\nmainland of Dare County, N. C.\nIn making this ahnouncement I\nwish to express my gratitude to\nthe 1?ood people of Dare County\nfor having honored me with the\nprivilege of serving them as their\ncommissioner and to thank them\nfor their past generous support of\nmy' candidacy. If re-elected to this\npost I shall as in the past do my\nvery best to serve all sections of\nthe county alike, being fair and\nsquare to all concerned and consi\nder carefully any matters that\nmight come before our Board, I\nbelieve in good schools, good roads\nand lower taxes in keeping with\ngood County Government. I earn\nestly solicit your vote and support\nagain and hope and trust that the\nduties of the office of the County\nCommissioners have been dis\ncharged in such a manner as to\nhave met with your approval and\nto merit your continued support\nin the coming Primary- May 31,\n1958.\nC. C. DUVALL\nManns Harbor, N. C.\n6 YEARS OLD\nGlenmore\nKENTUCKY STRAIGHT\nBOURBON |P|| S 6 PROOF\nfr\u2019arMTW laSI\nGlenmorel\nGLENMORE O.ST.UER.ES\nANNOUNCES CANDIDACY\nFOR COUNTY COMMISSIONER\nI announce myself a candidate\nfor Commissioner representing\nthe Mainland District, Dare Coun\nty, N. C., subject to the May Pri\nmary. I solicit your vote and sup\nport in the forthcoming election.\nMy decision to present myself as\na candidate for this office was\nmade after considering the many\nrequests from citizens of this dis\ntrict as well as from other parts\nof the county. My sole interest is\nto serve all sections of the county\nto the best of my ability; if elected\nI shall work toward that end.\nHORACE B. HOOPER\nStumpy Point, N. C.\n-4-11-7tc\nADMINISTRATOR\u2019S NOTICE\nHaving qualified as Administra\ntrix of the estate of Dennett Hen\nry Ransom of Frisco, Dare County,\nNorth Carolina, this is to notify\nall persons having claims against\nthe estate of said Dennett Henry\nRansom to present them to the\nundersigned within one year from\ndate of this notice or same will\nbe pleaded in bar of their recovery.\nAll persons indebted to said estate\nplease make immediate payment.\nThis the 28th day of April, 1958.\nELLA MAY RANSOM\nFrisco, N. C.\nT-5-2-6tc\nADMINISTRATOR\u2019S NOTICE\nHaving qualified as Executor of\nthe estate of Daisy H. Midgett of\nNags Head, Dare County, North\nCarolina, this is to notify all per\nsons having claims against the\nestate of said Daisy H. Midgett,\nto present them to the undersigned\nwithin one year from date of this\nnotice or same will be pleaded in\nbar of their recovery. All persons\nindebted to said estate please make\nimmediate payment.\nThis the 3rd day of May, 1958.\nCORNELIUS P. MIDGETT\nNags Head, N. C.\nWorth and Horner, Attorney.\nT-5-9-6tc\nNOTICE\nNORTH CAROLINA\nDARE COUNTY\nThe undersigned having duly\nqualified as the administrator of\nthe Estate of Melton V. Hooper,\ndeceased, late of the above named\ncounty and state, all persons hav\ning claims of whatsoever nature\nagainst the said Melton V. Hooper,\ndeceased, are hereby notified to\nexhibit the said claim or claims to\nthe undersigned on or before the\n2nd day of May, 1959, or this\nnotice will be pleaded in bar of\ntheir recovery. All persons indebt\ned to the said Melton V. Hooper,\ndeceased, are hereby requested to\npay the said indebtedness to the\nundersigned immediately.\nThis the 2nd day of May, 1958.\nFLOYD L. HOOPER\nAdministrator\nT-5-2-6tc\nADMINISTRATOR\u2019S NOTICE\nNorth Carolina\nDare County.\nHaving qualified as Administra\ntor of the estate of Barte Bar\nnette, deceased, late of Dare\nCounty, North Carolina, this is to\nnotify all persons having claims\nagainst the estate of the said de\nceased to exhibit them to the un\ndersigned at Frisco, North Caro-\nlina, on or before the 15th day of\nApril, 1959, or this notice will be\npleaded in bar of their recovery.\nAll persons indebted to said estate\nwill please make immediate pay\nment.\nThis 15th day of April, 1958.\nBENNIE BARNETT,\nFrisco, North Carolina\nAdministrator\n-4-25-6tc\nNOTICE OF SALE\nBy virtue of the authority con\ntained in that certain Deed of\nTrust executed by Major M. Mor\nrisette and wife, Emma Weeks\nMorrisette, to Southern Loan and\nInsurance Company, Trustee, dated\nMarch 2, 1953, and recorded in\nBook 43, page 450, of the public\nregistry of Dare County, N. C.,\ndefault having been made in the\nconditions thereof, the said Trustee\nwill, on the 3rd day of June, 1958.\nat 12 o\u2019clock Noon, at the Court\nhouse door of Dare County, N. C.,\noffer for sale at public auction to\nthe highest bidder for cash the\nfollowing described property:\nSituate in Atlantic Township.\nDare County, North Carolina, to\nwit:\nAll that certain lot or parcel\nof land, together with the houses\nand improvements thereon, ly\ning and being near Kill Devil\n\u2019Hills in Atlantic Township, Dare\nCounty, N. C., and known as,\ndesignated and being Lot No. 28,\nas shown on plat \u201cB\u201d of the sub\ndivision known as Virginia Dare\nShores. Map or plat of said plat\n\u201cB\u201d of Virginia Dare Shores\nduly recorded in Book 17, page\n105, office of the Register of\nDeeds of Dare County, N. C M\nreference to which is hereby\nmade for a more particular de\nscription thereof.\nSaid lot fronting fifty (50)\nfeet on the East side of U. S.\nHighway No. 158 sometimes\nknown as Virginia Dare Trail,\nand extending Eastwardly be\ntween parallel lines to the At\nlantic Ocean.\nSame being the lands conveyed\nto M. M. Morrisette, Jr. by Gra\nham W. Bell et ux by deed dated\nJuly 3, 1936, and duly recorded\nin Book 17, page 268, office of\"\nthe Register of Deeds of Dare\nCounty, N. C.\nThe above property will be sold\nsubject to taxes for the year 1958.\nA deposit of 5 per cent of the.\namount bid will be required of the\nsuccessful bidder at the hour of\nsale.\nThis Notice dated and Posted\nthis 3rd dav of May, 1958.\nSOUTHERN LOAN\nINSURANCE COMPANY,\nTRUSTEE.\nBy Worth and Homer\nAttorneys\nT-5-9-4tc\nPAGE SEVEN","height":"24948","width":"18379"}}
